@startuml seat_comfort_to_massage_intensity_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Seat Comfort To Massage Intensity Signal Flow\n(BCM comfort commands -> MSC massage intensity)

participant "BCM comfort commands" as BCM #F4F7FB
participant "MSC\nseat massage owner" as MSC #E8F7E8
participant "Seat massage bus" as SeatBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / panels" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Comfort Inputs ==

BCM -> MSC : gSeatHeatLvl\ngSeatVentLvl\ndriveComfortMode\nseatDetail freshness
MSC -> MSC : if seat detail stale\nthen seatHeatLvl = 0 / seatVentLvl = 0
MSC -> MSC : if driveComfortMode >= 1\nmassageIntensity = 20 + driveComfortMode * 10
MSC -> MSC : if seatHeatLvl >= 2 or seatVentLvl >= 2\nmassageIntensity = 30 + heat*12 + vent*8
note right of MSC
Representative intensity inputs
- seatHeatLvl / seatVentLvl
- driveComfortMode
- seat-detail freshness
end note

== Massage Publish ==

MSC -> MSC : clamp massageIntensity to 0..100
MSC -> SeatBus : frmMassageStateMsg\nMassageIntensity / MassageState
note right of MSC
Representative outputs
- MassageIntensity
- MassageState
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

SeatBus -> Obs : seat comfort /\nmassage readback

note over BCM, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. BCM-derived seat comfort commands reach MSC
2. MSC converts comfort demand into massage intensity
3. Massage state is published on the seat comfort path
4. Observers expose the comfort-to-massage coupling
end note

@enduml
